{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"180509f3-2595-40e6-b9dc-f2e71539c6d4","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_HLU0Bi9Ord2RoUsujQFY9E","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-c3e5145613204389a957be25ff7b1aeb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-c3e5145613204389a957be25ff7b1aeb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"37a9badd-3b7f-444c-82ba-eea40f7f7bb6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, the file compilation order matters. Files can only reference types and modules defined in files listed *before* them in the project file.\n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```xml\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n```\n\n`Services.fs` is listed first but it depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`). `Domain.fs` is listed second, so `Services.fs` can't see it. The correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines types, no dependencies)\n\n\n2. `Services.fs` (depends on Domain)\n3. `Program.fs` (depends on both Domain and Services)","outputTokens":476,"requestId":"5C24:2F61F4:5D7CEDA:66520DB:69F1560B"},"id":"d9536d4b-9255-4f91-b0fd-0530b03489f5","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:51:31.525Z","parentId":"2932f24d-6fdd-4464-a161-0e0488f30723"}
